A `.gitignore` file for Python and Jupyter Notebook projects tells git to ignore files and folders that are auto-generated or not needed in the repository, making the repo cleaner and safer to share.[5][6]

### Typical `.gitignore` for Python & Jupyter Notebook

```
# Byte-compiled / optimized files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# Distribution / packaging
build/
dist/
.eggs/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg

# Virtual environments
env/
venv/
ENV/
.venv/
.python-version

# Logs and databases
*.log
*.sqlite3

# Test outputs
.tox/
.pytest_cache/
cover/
coverage.*
*.cover
*.pyc
.cache
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml
*.spec

# Jupyter Notebook checkpoints
.ipynb_checkpoints

# saved models
.saved_models

# Environment variables and secrets
.env
.env.*
*.env

# Editor and IDE specific
.vscode/
.idea/
*.sublime-workspace
*.sublime-project
.history
# pptx
.pptx
